services.name: Emergency Food Pantry
services.description: Free groceries and emergency food assistance for families and individuals facing food insecurity. Includes fresh produce, canned goods, and household essentials.
services.interpretation_services: Spanish and Arabic interpreters available on request
services.application_process: No application required. Valid ID and proof of address needed for first visit.
services.fees_description: No fees - all services provided free of charge
services.eligibility_description: Open to all residents of Example County experiencing food insecurity

services.name: Mobile Food Pantry
services.description: Mobile food distribution service bringing fresh groceries directly to underserved communities and areas with limited transportation access.
services.application_process: No appointment needed - first come, first served
services.eligibility_description: Available to all community members - no income restrictions

services.name: Community Meals Program
services.description: Free hot meals served daily in a welcoming community environment. Nutritious, home-cooked meals prepared by volunteers and staff.
services.eligibility_description: Open to all community members regardless of income or housing status

services.name: Food Pantry Service
services.description: Client-choice food pantry allowing families to select groceries based on their preferences and dietary needs.
services.application_process: Simple intake form required for first visit
services.eligibility_description: Residents of Example City with household income below 200% of federal poverty level

services.name: Home-Delivered Meals
services.description: Nutritious meals delivered directly to homebound seniors and individuals with disabilities who cannot prepare their own meals.
services.application_process: Assessment required - call to schedule intake appointment
services.fees_description: Sliding scale fees based on income - no one turned away for inability to pay
services.eligibility_description: Adults 60+ or individuals with disabilities who are homebound and unable to prepare meals

services.name: Mobile Food Pantry - Route A
services.description: Mobile food distribution serving rural communities with limited access to food resources. Includes fresh produce, dairy, and pantry staples.
services.eligibility_description: Available to all residents in service area

services.name: Mobile Food Pantry - Route B
services.description: Mobile food distribution focusing on urban food deserts and low-income housing areas.
services.eligibility_description: Open to all community members in service area

services.name: Community Soup Kitchen
services.description: Daily hot meals served in a dignified, restaurant-style setting. Meals prepared with love by volunteer cooks.
services.eligibility_description: Open to anyone in need of a meal

services.name: Faith-Based Food Pantry
services.description: Food pantry service operated by faith community, welcoming people of all backgrounds and beliefs.
services.application_process: Brief intake form on first visit
services.eligibility_description: Open to all individuals and families experiencing food insecurity

services.name: Student Food Pantry
services.description: Food pantry specifically serving college students facing food insecurity. Includes grab-and-go meals and grocery items.
services.eligibility_description: Current Example University students, staff, and faculty

services.name: Fresh Produce Distribution
services.description: Distribution of fresh, locally-sourced fruits and vegetables to food pantries and community organizations.
services.application_process: Partner organizations must complete application process
services.fees_description: Minimal handling fees for partner organizations
services.eligibility_description: Serves qualified nonprofit organizations and food pantries

services.name: School Backpack Program
services.description: Weekend food program providing students with backpacks filled with nutritious, kid-friendly foods for weekends and school breaks.
services.application_process: Referral through school counselors and teachers
services.eligibility_description: Students identified by school staff as experiencing food insecurity

services.name: Summer Meals Program
services.description: Free nutritious meals for children during summer months when school meals are not available.
services.application_process: No application required - open to all children
services.eligibility_description: Children and teens aged 18 and under

services.name: Emergency Food Response
services.description: Rapid deployment of emergency food assistance during natural disasters, community crises, and other emergencies.
services.application_process: Activated during declared emergencies - no application needed
services.eligibility_description: Available to all community members affected by declared emergencies

services.name: Senior Congregate Meals
services.description: Nutritious meals served in a social setting for seniors, providing both nourishment and social interaction.
services.fees_description: Suggested donation - no one turned away for inability to pay
services.eligibility_description: Adults aged 60 and over

services.name: Weekend Food Bags
services.description: Discreet food bags sent home with students on Fridays to ensure they have nutritious food over the weekend.
services.eligibility_description: Students in participating schools experiencing food insecurity

services.name: Interfaith Food Pantry Network
services.description: Collaborative network of faith-based food pantries serving diverse communities throughout Example County.
services.eligibility_description: Open to all residents regardless of faith background

services.name: Food Recovery and Redistribution
services.description: Rescue and redistribution of surplus food from retailers and restaurants to food pantries and meal programs.
services.application_process: Partner registration required for receiving organizations
services.fees_description: Minimal handling fees for partner organizations
services.eligibility_description: Qualified nonprofit organizations and food distribution programs

services.name: WIC (Women, Infants, and Children) Program
services.description: Federal nutrition program providing healthy foods, nutrition education, and breastfeeding support to low-income pregnant women, new mothers, and children under 5.
services.eligibility_description: Pregnant women, breastfeeding mothers, and children under 5 meeting income guidelines

services.name: SNAP Outreach and Application Assistance
services.description: Assistance with SNAP (food stamps) applications, recertification, and navigation of the benefits system.
services.eligibility_description: Available to all community members seeking SNAP benefits

services.name: Community Food Co-op Pantry
services.description: Sliding-scale food pantry integrated with community-owned grocery store, providing affordable access to healthy foods.
services.eligibility_description: Co-op members experiencing financial hardship
